g.text: I'm assuming you don't mean that literally.

g.title: j3670679630
g.text: She was born two minutes before me at a minute to midnight, and she thinks she's a hundred years wiser.

g.title: j3257685916
g.text: I just don't know how to help her anymore.

g.title: j2945753200
g.text: Oh for f-- I didn't mean that bloody literally, mate.

g.text: No, I don't mean that bloody literally, mate.

g.title: j508049835
g.text: She's hurting. And she's alone. And when she's like that...she goes dark.

g.title: j4258658562
g.text: We've always been on the same wavelength. Twins and all.

g.title: j2731078406
g.text: Wouldn't that make it easier?

g.title: j2300813281
g.text: I can see why that'd make things harder...

g.title: j1535290424
g.text: And I don't mean normal dark. "Crystals and cards and ghosts" dark. I mean *pit of the void* dark.

g.title: j1020750030
g.text: It's one thing when you're twins and share a wavelength. It's another thing when she's literally *in* your thoughts.

g.title: j411916850
g.text: When I need her to listen to reason, all she hears is *motives* and *feelings.*

g.title: j61309193
g.text: Listening to your intentions rather than your words.

g.title: j1662246443
g.text: And you're worried someday she won't come back?

g.title: j1248689774
g.text: When I use Transference on Eleanor, I can hear what she hears. I don't blame her for having dark moments.

g.title: j401334927
g.text: Yeah, not gonna lie, it creeps me out.

g.text: Can I make a suggestion?

g.title: j3543717359
g.text: Yikes.

g.title: j907516435

g.title: j3616588142

g.title: j1405963352

g.title: j1206587946

g.text: She's stronger than you give her credit for.

g.text: She'll be fine.

g.title: j3622556362
g.text: AUGH

g.text: Trust me, I know how proper tough she is.

g.title: j2283914893
g.text: As okay as someone can be, when her friends treat her like a monster.

g.title: j3749430893
g.text: As okay as she can be, when her own twin brother doesn't know how to talk to her anymore.

g.title: j1363943977
g.text: She can hear every thought of everybody around her--and has to try to keep a straight face. I'd go dark now and again, too.

g.title: j2943149490
g.text: I'm not so sure. I don't think any of us can understand what she's going through.

g.title: j379590549
g.text: Hard to read your mind that way. And sometimes it's easier to communicate in text. Case in point, look at us.
